  "articleSummary": "The article argues that teams should master all three Postgres-native search tools—full-text search (tsvector/GIN), trigrams (pg_trgm), and exact-match indexes (B-tree/hash)—rather than relying on just one or prematurely adopting a dedicated search service. It presents a decision framework based on query shape: exact words vs. meaning, and short vs. long text. The tone is tutorial and practical, using a \"tool map\" metaphor to guide readers in matching the right tool to the problem. The intended audience is development teams who want to ship better search with less complexity.",
